---
title: Linguine and Zucchini with Sweet Italian Sausage in a Tomato Sauce
description: We’re in peak zucchini season right now, when the green veg is at is juiciest and sweetest. What better way to celebrate than with a pasta dish? Italy is where the zucchini as we know it was first cultivated, after all, plus it gets its name from the Italian word for “squash.” Here, it’s tossed with sausage crumbles, a hearty tomato sauce, and strands of linguine for a dish that’s positively gourd-geous.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/linguine-and-zucchini-06925daf.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/linguine-and-zucchini-b264527d.pdf
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 830 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 86 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 840 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/linguine-and-zucchini-59318fd3043c3c016f127bc2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil.

Trim ends from @zucchini{2}(quartered lengthwise), then quarter lengthwise. Thinly slice quarters crosswise into triangles. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{2}(thinly sliced). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Cut @lemon{1}(cut into wedges). Remove @Italian pork sausage{18%ounce} from casing; discard casing.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook, breaking meat up into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Once water boils, add @linguine{12%ounce} to #pot{} and cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve @pasta cooking water{1%cup}, then drain. Return linguine to pot along with a splash of cooking water.

Add onion, zucchini, and another large drizzle of olive oil to pan used for sausage over medium-high heat. Cook, tossing, until softened, about ~{4-6%minutes}. Toss in garlic, @dried thyme{2%tsp}, and @chili flakes{1%tsp} (to taste). Cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @diced tomatoes{2%can} and sausage to pan with veggies and stir to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Let simmer until rest of meal is ready.

> TIP: Give the sauce a taste. If it seems sharp, add up to 1 tsp sugar.

Add sausage, veggies, and sauce to pot with linguine. Add a squeeze or two of lemon (to taste). Toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce seems thick or stiff, stir in more pasta cooking water.

Divide mixture between plates and sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}. Cut any remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side for squeezing over.